  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "Music can evoke a wide range of emotions, and many songs are known for their ability to touch listeners deeply and even bring them to tears. Here are some songs that are often cited as particularly emotional:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton** - Written about the loss of his son, this song expresses profound grief and longing.\n\n2. **\"Hallelujah\" by Jeff Buckley (originally by Leonard Cohen)** - Buckley's rendition carries a haunting quality that resonates with many listeners.\n\n3. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay** - This song offers comfort in times of sorrow and is often seen as a message of support.\n\n4. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - Adele's powerful vocals and heartfelt lyrics about loss and heartbreak can be incredibly moving.\n\n5. **\"Creep\" by Radiohead** - The themes of alienation and self-doubt in this song resonate with many people.\n\n6. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron** - This song captures longing and nostalgia in a way that many find relatable.\n\n7. **\"Everybody Hurts\" by R.E.M.** - This song offers reassurance to those feeling overwhelmed by their emotions.\n\n8. **\"Breathe Me\" by Sia** - The vulnerability and emotion in Sia's performance often leave listeners in tears.\n\n9. **\"Dance With My Father\" by Luther Vandross** - This touching tribute to his father explores themes of love and loss.\n\n10. **\"When We Were Young\" by Adele** - Reflecting on nostalgia and the passage of time, this song can evoke strong emotions.\n\nEveryone's emotional triggers are different, so what makes one person cry might resonate differently with another. Feel free to explore these and see which ones may resonate with you!",
